lattice3dshell_combined_n4.out
Shell-mode lattice3d combined test (LatticeFrameElastic, N=4): all 6 dofs prescribed at free end.
StaticStructural nsteps 1 rtolv 1.e-6 ddm 12 2 1 2 2 2 3 2 4 2 5 2 6 ddv 6 1.e-4 1.e-4 1.e-4 1.e-3 1.e-3 1.e-3 ddltf 2 nmodules 1
errorcheck
domain 3dLattice
OutputManager tstep_all dofman_all element_all
ndofman 2 nelem 1 ncrosssect 1 nmat 1 nbc 1 nic 0 nltf 2
node 1 coords 3 0.000000e+00 0.000000e+00 0.000000e+00 bc 6 1 1 1 1 1 1
node 2 coords 3 1.000000e+00 0.000000e+00 0.000000e+00 bc 6 0 0 0 0 0 0
lattice3D 1 nodes 2 1 2 crossSect 1 mat 1 shellnormal 3 0.0 0.0 1.0 polycoords 12 0.5 -0.05 -0.005   0.5 0.05 -0.005   0.5 0.05 0.005   0.5 -0.05 0.005
latticecs 1 material 1 nlayers 4
latticeframeelastic 1 d 2400. tAlpha 0.0 E 30.e9 n 0.0
BoundaryCondition 1 loadTimeFunction 1 prescribedvalue 0.0
ConstantFunction 1 f(t) 1.
PiecewiseLinFunction 2 nPoints 2 t 2 0. 1. f(t) 2 0. 1.
#%BEGIN_CHECK% tolerance 1.e-1
## N=4 (hybrid: 4 layer IPs + 1 centroid IP). Must match the N=1 reference
## bit-for-bit in the linear-elastic limit: per-IP cross-section partitioning
## (axial + own through-thickness bending on layers; shear + torsion + in-plane
## bending on centroid) reproduces the single-IP stiffness exactly.
#REACTION tStep 1 number 1 dof 1 value -3.0000e+3
#REACTION tStep 1 number 1 dof 2 value  6.0000e+3
#REACTION tStep 1 number 1 dof 3 value -9.0000e+3
#REACTION tStep 1 number 1 dof 4 value -2.5000e-1
#REACTION tStep 1 number 1 dof 5 value  4.4997e+3
#REACTION tStep 1 number 1 dof 6 value  2.9750e+3
#%END_CHECK%
